-----------------
Throws exception
-----------------
  ** throws_unchecked_exception("filename.text");
  ** throws_checked_exception("filename.text")

The throw keyword, can be used to throw only one exception at a time, but we can declare multiple exceptions with throws

--------------------------------------------
Overriding methods with the throws clause
--------------------------------------------

  ** over_riding_methods_with_exceptions()

The method being overridden in the child class has the option to either not throw the exception or throw a subclass of the exception declared in the parent methodâ€™s signature.

--------------------------
Creating Custom Exceptions
--------------------------

//Checked Exception
class MyCustomException extends Exception { 
    
    MyCustomException(String message){
      super(message);
    }
}

//Unchecked Exception
class MyCustomException extends RuntimeException { 
    
    MyCustomException(String message){
      super(message);
    }
}
